Conclusion

The highest number of matches were played in the years : 2013, 2014, 2015.

Mumbai Indians team won highest number of matches (4 out of 12 maatches).

Teams that chose bowling first has the higher chance of winning than teams that choose to bat first.

After winning toss, more teams choose to fielding first.

In finals, teams that decided to fielding first won the matches than the team that do batting first.

In finals, after winning toss more teams choose to do fielding first.

Top players of match were CH gayle, AB de villers.

Out of 12 final matches, the team that won the toss 9 times also won the IPL final.

Highest number of fours' were hit by player : Shikar Dhawan

Highest number of sixes were hit by player : CH Gayle

Top Scorers : Virat Kohli, SK Raina, RG Sharma

The highest number of matches were played by : SK RAina, RG Sharma

Dismissals was most by catch out.

Most Wickets were taken by SL Malinga.

By observing the above conclusions, we can observe that: Most Successful Team is Mumbai Indians

Successful players are CH Gayle and SK Raina

Winning or losing the toss and choosing feilding or batting fisrt contributes to the win or loss of the team.
